ANNOUNCEMENTS (04): PRO/MBDS SEEKING INFECTIOUS DISEASE MODERATOR
************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tues 16 Jul 2013
From: Marjorie P. Pollack, MD <pollack@promedmail.org>


Infectious Disease Moderator for PRO/MBDS
-----------------------------------------------
ProMED, the Program for Monitoring Emerging Diseases of the International Society for Infectious Diseases, is seeking a highly qualified individual to fill a position of an Infectious Disease Moderator covering human diseases for the PRO/MBDS regional network. The individual will join an international team of over 40 global health specialists located in 25 countries.

PRO/MBDS is regional network that focuses on the 6 countries in the Mekong Basin Region. These countries include The Kingdom of Cambodia, Yunnan province and the Guangxi Autonomous Republic of the People's Republic of China, Lao People's Democratic Republic, The Union of Myanmar, The Socialist Republic of Viet Nam, and the Kingdom of Thailand. Coverage of events outside of the region with potential importance to the region is also expected. The infectious diseases moderator will work closely with the PRO/MBDS Regional moderator, other PRO/MBDS moderators and the ProMED-mail Deputy Editor.

This position requires a strong background in infectious diseases and sound English writing skills. Applicants must be willing to check their e-mail at least twice-daily and have regular access to the Internet, 7 days per week.

Responsibilities:
1. Monitor and post relevant reports of events of interest in human health to the MBDS region using an online dashboard tool in a timely way (less than 24 hours).
2. Respond to specific requests for posting of human health reports communicated by ProMED participants and staff.
3. Provide appropriate contextual commentary and background for these reports.
4. Attend periodic meetings (annual or biannual) of ProMED staff.
5. Maintain expertise in human infectious diseases through continuing education.
6. Assist in training of new staff.
7. Assist in recruitment of new subscribers and outreach at local and regional professional conferences and meetings.

Qualifications:
1. An advanced degree in the human health field required (MD, MBBS, PhD in microbiology or equivalent), additional advanced degree in a related field preferred (MPH or participation in an international Field Epidemiology Training Programme);
2. Extensive experience in human infectious diseases including zoonotic diseases;
3. A track record of achievement in academic, governmental or nongovernmental organization commensurate with career stage;
4. Fluency in written and spoken English and strong written communication skills; skills in one or more of the PRO/MBDS country languages a plus;
5. Skillful in use of Internet resources and facility with electronic communication;
6. Residence in one of the PRO/MBDS focus countries a plus.

The position requires daily monitoring of e-mail and websites requiring an average of one hour a day. Compensation is a modest stipend paid quarterly, reimbursement for Internet expenses and travel to ProMED staff/editorial meetings.

Interested individuals should forward a cover letter and curriculum vitae to: <info@isid.org>.

--
Marjorie P. Pollack, MD
Deputy Editor, ProMED-mail
<pollack@promedmail.org>

